---
description: Backend architecture rules
globs: ["apps/api/**"]
---
- Anatomy (apps/api/src): `modules/<feature>/{api/{controller,dto},application/{use-case,service},domain/,infrastructure/,adapters/,model/,lib/}`
  plus cross-cutting `src/core` (logger, errors, validation, rate-limit, openapi, http), `src/config`, `src/bootstrap` (Fastify assembly).
- One-way flow: Controller → Application (use-case/service) → Domain → Infrastructure/Adapters.
- Controllers (`api/*.controller.ts`): HTTP binding only, exactly one delegation per handler — no logic/SDK/env/repository access.
- Use-cases orchestrate services + transactions; services stay focused and small; domain stays pure.
- Repositories (`infrastructure/*.repository.ts`): persistence only, parameterized, bounded.
- Adapters wrap every external SDK. Only `GeminiAdapter` may import the Gemini SDK.
- Validation via the shared Zod pipe at the boundary (class-validator forbidden).
- Errors: typed `AppError` with messageKey `errors.<feature>.<key>`; global exception filter sanitizes — never leak provider errors or stack traces.
- Logging via `AppLogger` (pino) from `src/core` only. Rate limiting via the throttler in `src/core`.
- Only `src/config` (zod-validated, fail-fast) reads `process.env`.
